me.taylorkelly.mywarp.teleport

Class TeleportService

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.taylorkelly.mywarp.teleport.TeleportService

  • public final class TeleportService
extends java.lang.Object
    Teleports an entity after the teleport position has been validated using a previously registered PositionValidationStrategy.

    For raw teleports use LocalEntity.teleport(LocalWorld, Vector3, EulerDirection).

    • Method Detail

      • teleport

        public TeleportService.TeleportStatus teleport(LocalEntity entity,
                                               LocalWorld world,
                                               Vector3 position,
                                               EulerDirection rotation)
        Teleports the given entity to the given position in the given world and sets its rotation to the given one.

        Implementations must return a TeleportService.TeleportStatus that represents the status of the individual teleport.

        Parameters:
        entity - the entity to teleport
        world - the world to teleport to
        position - the position to teleport to
        rotation - the rotation to teleport to
        Returns:
        The resulting TeleportStatus
